<p>Manulife Financial Corporation, the parent of Manulife Financial, John Hancock
Financial Services, and Maritime Life is the fifth largest insurer in the world,
serving millions of customers in 19 countries and territories.

<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Requirements</font>

<p>Manulife’s application development team recognized that their software tools,
architecture, and development life cycle process, while serviceable, might not be
sufficiently scalable to achieve the growth objectives established for the company
and often impeded the ability of the technology organization to efficiently respond
to the evolving business needs.  Manulife decided to review and find opportunities
to improve their development process, tools, and overall architecture.
<p>Manulife asked Nevo to work closely with their development team to identify the
right technology platform for future development, and to help guide the Manulife
development team to a more robust, repeatable development lifecycle approach and
application architecture.


<p><font class="sectionTitleText">Nevo's Solution</font>

<p>Using the Microsoft .NET framework, Nevo led Manulife’s development team to re-implement
substantial sections of the ManulifeUSA.com public and internal website while actively
mentoring the Manulife team through an effective, efficient, scalable development lifecycle
process that can sustain the growing organization.  Tools included VB.NET, ASP.NET, ADO.NET,
SQL Server, Vignette content retrieval, and unit testing tools, NUnit and NUnitASP.

<p>This development effort resulted in the successful deployment of Manulife’s first .NET
implementation, and this architecture and development process is currently being used as
a model for continued migration to .NET.  The Nevo team remains actively involved as
consultants on further architecture refinement and detailed design, while also delivering
key functional elements of the ManulifeUSA.com application.



